CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 11, 1961, pg. 25, reads: "Happy Birthday - Robin Bullard, aided by many of her little friends, celebrated her birthday last Saturday with a delightful party given at 2801 Bedford Ave., the home of her parents, Robin (shown cutting the cake) was escorted by 'Champ' Andrews. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Woman standing over Robin Bullard wearing striped hat and cutting sheet cake, on her third birthday, surrounded by other girls, and boys, possibly including "Champ" Andrews wearing plaid jacket, in kitchen of Bullard home, 2801 Bedford Avenue
